"title": "1315: God, as redeemer",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1315",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God alone has the ability to save his people from slavery and captivity. God's redemptive will and power is demonstrated in his deliverance of Israel from bondage in Egypt, and supremely through the death and resurrection of Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>God as the sole redeemer of Israel</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa47:4\">ISA 47:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut13:5\">DEU 13:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:14\">PSA 19:14</a></p>\n<h3>He redeems because of his love</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:8\">DEU 7:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:26\">PSA 44:26</a></p>\n<h3>He is able to redeem because of his power</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:26\">DEU 9:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:23\">2SA 7:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:21\">1CH 17:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:10\">NEH 1:10</a></p>\n<h2>God acts as Israel's redeemer</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:35\">PSA 78:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps111:9\">PSA 111:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:1\">ISA 43:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:17\">ISA 48:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:5\">ISA 54:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:16\">ISA 63:16</a></p>\n<h3>He promises to redeem Israel from Egypt</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:8-Exod3:10\">EXO 3:8–3:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:21\">EXO 3:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:4\">EXO 14:4</a></p>\n<h3>He redeems Israel in the exodus from Egypt</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:15\">DEU 5:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:15\">DEU 15:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:8\">DEU 21:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:18\">DEU 24:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:9-Neh9:11\">NEH 9:9–9:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:14-Ps77:20\">PSA 77:14–77:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:23-Ps105:38\">PSA 105:23–105:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos13:4\">HOS 13:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:4\">MIC 6:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:30-Acts7:36\">ACT 7:30–7:36</a></p>\n<h3>He redeems Israel from Babylonian exile</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:14\">ISA 41:14</a></strong> <em>“Redeemer” is a characteristic title for God in the second part of Isaiah.  In the context of the exile Isaiah reminds Israel that God would act as redeemer.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:4\">ISA 43:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:6\">ISA 44:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:24\">ISA 44:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:26\">ISA 49:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:5\">ISA 54:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa60:16\">ISA 60:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa62:12\">ISA 62:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:33-Jer50:35\">JER 50:33–50:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:12\">JER 51:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:10\">MIC 4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech10:8\">ZEC 10:8</a></p>\n<h2>God redeems his people from difficult personal circumstances</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:22\">PSA 34:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:22\">ISA 29:22</a> <em>Abraham was redeemed from the land of idolatry to become God's servant</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:25\">JOB 19:25</a> <em>Job, in the midst of his despair, declares God to be his redeemer</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:4-Ps31:5\">PSA 31:4–31:5</a> <em>part of the psalmist's prayer for deliverance when confronted by an evil conspiracy</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:58\">LAM 3:58</a> <em>the lamentor recognises personal redemption within the context of national despair</em></p>\n<h3>He brings deliverance from enemies</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:18\">PSA 69:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:10\">PSA 106:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:2\">PSA 107:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer15:21\">JER 15:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:11\">JER 31:11</a></p>\n<h2>God redeems his people from the bondage and guilt of sin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps130:7-Ps130:8\">PSA 130:7–130:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:22\">PSA 34:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:20\">ISA 59:20</a></p>\n<h3>Those who remain sinful do not find redemption</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos7:13\">HOS 7:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps26:11\">PSA 26:11</a> <em>The request for redemption is made on the basis of uprightness</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:27-Isa1:28\">ISA 1:27–1:28</a></p>\n<h2>God redeems his people from death</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:15\">PSA 49:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:25-Job19:27\">JOB 19:25–19:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:4\">PSA 103:4</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ is central to God's redemptive purposes</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:13-Col1:14\">COL 1:13–1:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:68\">LUK 1:68</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:23-Rom3:24\">ROM 3:23–3:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:30\">1CO 1:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:23\">1CO 7:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:13-Gal3:14\">GAL 3:13–3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4-Gal4:5\">GAL 4:4–4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:7\">EPH 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:11-Heb9:12\">HEB 9:11–9:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:18-1Pet1:21\">1PE 1:18–1:21</a></p>\n<h3>God will finally redeem all creation at Jesus Christ's second coming</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:19-Rom8:23\">ROM 8:19–8:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:28\">LUK 21:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:13-Eph1:14\">EPH 1:13–1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:30\">EPH 4:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:13-Titus2:14\">TIT 2:13–2:14</a></p>\n<h2>God's redemptive work brings him praise and worship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:3-Eph1:7\">EPH 1:3–1:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:1-Exod15:21\">EXO 15:1–15:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:23\">PSA 71:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps111:9\">PSA 111:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:134\">PSA 119:134</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps136:1-Ps136:26\">PSA 136:1–136:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:4-Isa35:10\">ISA 35:4–35:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:22-Isa44:23\">ISA 44:22–44:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:20\">ISA 48:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:11\">ISA 51:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:9\">ISA 52:9</a></p>",
